==Season 4== In a 2011 interview, cast member John Witherspoon announced that the series had been renewed for a fourth season, which will consist of 20 episodes. Voice Casting director Andrea Romano stated at Comic Con 2011 that season four of ''The Boondocks'' is headed into production despite no official confirmation from either Aaron McGruder or Adult Swim.<ref>{{cite news | title = 'The Boondocks' Season 4 Is In The Works. | url = http://screenrant.com/the-boondocks-season-4-announced-kofi-125008/ | work = Kofi Outlaw | publisher = Screen Rant | date=2011-07-23 }} </ref>
